---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Edge Cases & Gotchas - CSRF Protection">
	<main>
		<a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to Home</a>
		
		<h1>Edge Cases & Common Gotchas</h1>
		
		<section>
			<h2>When CSRF Protection Fires</h2>
			<p>Understanding the execution order is critical:</p>
			
			<div class="flow-diagram">
				<div class="flow-step">
					<strong>1. Request Arrives</strong>
					<p>Browser sends HTTP request</p>
				</div>
				<div class="arrow">↓</div>
				<div class="flow-step highlight">
					<strong>2. CSRF Validation (Built-in)</strong>
					<p>Astro checks CSRF token BEFORE middleware</p>
					<p class="note">❗ This happens automatically</p>
				</div>
				<div class="arrow">↓</div>
				<div class="flow-step">
					<strong>3. Your Middleware</strong>
					<p>Custom middleware runs (src/middleware.ts)</p>
				</div>
				<div class="arrow">↓</div>
				<div class="flow-step">
					<strong>4. Route Handler</strong>
					<p>Your page/API code executes</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="warning-box">
				<h3>⚠️ Key Point</h3>
				<p>
					<strong>CSRF validation happens BEFORE your middleware!</strong>
					If the token is invalid, your middleware never runs.
					This is by design - security first.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>Webhooks: The Classic Gotcha</h2>
			<p>
				Webhooks are external services calling YOUR API. They don't have CSRF tokens
				and shouldn't need them. They use signature verification instead.
			</p>
			
			<h3>The Problem:</h3>
			<pre><code>// ❌ This will fail with CSRF enabled!
// /api/webhook/stripe
export async function POST({ request }) {
  const signature = request.headers.get('stripe-signature');
  // Stripe sends no CSRF token
  // Astro rejects with 403 Forbidden
}</code></pre>
			
			<h3>The Solution: Exclude the Route</h3>
			<pre><code>// astro.config.mjs
export default defineConfig({
  output: 'server',
  security: {
    csrf: {
      exclude: [
        '/api/webhook/*',      // All webhook endpoints
        '/api/webhook/stripe', // Specific endpoint
        '/api/webhook/github',
      ]
    }
  }
});</code></pre>
			
			<h3>Common Webhook Providers:</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Stripe:</strong> Uses <code>stripe-signature</code> header</li>
				<li><strong>GitHub:</strong> Uses <code>x-hub-signature-256</code> header</li>
				<li><strong>Twilio:</strong> Uses <code>x-twilio-signature</code> header</li>
				<li><strong>Shopify:</strong> Uses <code>x-shopify-hmac-sha256</code> header</li>
			</ul>
			
			<div class="tip-box">
				<h3>💡 Best Practice</h3>
				<p>
					Create a dedicated <code>/api/webhook/*</code> path for all webhooks.
					Exclude the entire path. Verify signatures in your webhook handlers.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>Public APIs: Another Common Case</h2>
			<p>
				Public API endpoints that use API keys or OAuth don't need CSRF protection.
				CSRF only applies to cookie-based authentication.
			</p>
			
			<h3>When to Exclude:</h3>
			<div class="comparison-grid">
				<div class="exclude-yes">
					<h4>✅ Exclude These:</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>API key authenticated endpoints</li>
						<li>OAuth/JWT authenticated endpoints</li>
						<li>Public read-only APIs</li>
						<li>Webhook receivers</li>
						<li>CORS-enabled public APIs</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="exclude-no">
					<h4>❌ Don't Exclude These:</h4>
					<ul>
						<li>User-facing forms</li>
						<li>Cookie/session authenticated endpoints</li>
						<li>Admin panels</li>
						<li>Account management endpoints</li>
						<li>Anything using session cookies</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<h3>Example: Public API</h3>
			<pre><code>// /api/public/data
// Uses API key in header, not cookies
// Should be excluded from CSRF

export async function POST({ request }) {
  const apiKey = request.headers.get('x-api-key');
  if (!isValidApiKey(apiKey)) {
    return new Response('Invalid API key', { status: 401 });
  }
  
  // Process request
}</code></pre>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>Middleware Execution Order Issues</h2>
			
			<h3>Problem: Can't Access Session Before CSRF</h3>
			<pre><code>// ❌ This middleware runs AFTER CSRF validation
// src/middleware.ts
export async function onRequest(context, next) {
  // If CSRF fails, this never runs!
  const session = await getSession(context.request);
  context.locals.user = session.user;
  return next();
}</code></pre>
			
			<h3>Impact:</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>You can't customize CSRF behavior based on session data</li>
				<li>You can't log failed CSRF attempts with user context</li>
				<li>Authentication middleware runs after CSRF validation</li>
			</ul>
			
			<h3>Workaround: Use Exclusions</h3>
			<p>
				If you need custom CSRF logic, exclude the route and implement
				your own validation in middleware:
			</p>
			<pre><code>// astro.config.mjs
export default defineConfig({
  security: {
    csrf: {
      exclude: ['/api/custom-csrf/*']
    }
  }
});

// src/middleware.ts
export async function onRequest(context, next) {
  if (context.url.pathname.startsWith('/api/custom-csrf')) {
    // Your custom CSRF logic here
    const token = context.request.headers.get('x-csrf-token');
    if (!validateCustomToken(token)) {
      return new Response('Invalid token', { status: 403 });
    }
  }
  return next();
}</code></pre>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>CORS and CSRF</h2>
			<p>
				CORS and CSRF protection work together but serve different purposes:
			</p>
			
			<table>
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>CORS</th>
						<th>CSRF</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>Controls which origins can make requests</td>
						<td>Validates requests are intentional</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Protects the caller</td>
						<td>Protects the user</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Optional headers</td>
						<td>Required token</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Browser-enforced</td>
						<td>Server-enforced</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>
			
			<h3>The Gotcha: CORS Preflight vs CSRF</h3>
			<pre><code>// ❌ CORS preflight (OPTIONS) has no CSRF token!
// This will fail if you don't handle it

// ✅ Astro automatically allows OPTIONS without CSRF
// But be aware of this when debugging</code></pre>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>SPA/Client-Side Apps</h2>
			<p>
				If you're building a Single Page Application that makes API calls,
				you need to include the CSRF token in requests:
			</p>
			
			<h3>Getting the Token:</h3>
			<pre><code>// Option 1: From cookie
function getCsrfToken() {
  const cookies = document.cookie.split('; ');
  const csrfCookie = cookies.find(c => c.startsWith('astro.csrf='));
  return csrfCookie ? csrfCookie.split('=')[1] : null;
}

// Option 2: From meta tag (if you add one)
const token = document.querySelector('meta[name="csrf-token"]')?.content;</code></pre>
			
			<h3>Sending the Token:</h3>
			<pre><code>// In fetch requests
fetch('/api/transfer', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    'X-CSRF-Token': getCsrfToken()
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({ amount: 100 })
});</code></pre>
			
			<h3>Common Mistake:</h3>
			<pre><code>// ❌ Forgetting to include token in AJAX requests
fetch('/api/action', {
  method: 'POST',
  body: JSON.stringify(data)
});
// → 403 Forbidden

// ✅ Include token
fetch('/api/action', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: { 'X-CSRF-Token': getCsrfToken() },
  body: JSON.stringify(data)
});
// → Success</code></pre>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>Development vs Production</h2>
			
			<h3>Development Gotchas:</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Hot reload:</strong> Tokens persist across reloads in dev</li>
				<li><strong>Multiple tabs:</strong> Each tab has its own session</li>
				<li><strong>Cookie scope:</strong> localhost vs 127.0.0.1 are different domains</li>
			</ul>
			
			<h3>Production Considerations:</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>HTTPS required:</strong> Secure cookies won't work over HTTP</li>
				<li><strong>Cookie domain:</strong> Set correctly for subdomains</li>
				<li><strong>SameSite:</strong> Set to 'Lax' or 'Strict' in production</li>
				<li><strong>Load balancers:</strong> Ensure session affinity if needed</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>Debugging CSRF Issues</h2>
			
			<h3>Check 1: Is CSRF Active?</h3>
			<pre><code>// Only active in SSR/hybrid mode
// Check your astro.config.mjs:
export default defineConfig({
  output: 'server' // or 'hybrid' - CSRF active
  // output: 'static' - CSRF not active
});</code></pre>
			
			<h3>Check 2: Inspect the Token</h3>
			<ol>
				<li>Open DevTools → Application → Cookies</li>
				<li>Look for <code>astro.csrf</code> cookie</li>
				<li>Inspect form HTML for hidden <code>astro.csrf.token</code> field</li>
				<li>Check Network tab for token in POST requests</li>
			</ol>
			
			<h3>Check 3: Verify Exclusions</h3>
			<pre><code>// Add logging to see what's excluded
security: {
  csrf: {
    exclude: ['/api/webhook/*'],
    onInvalidToken: (request) => {
      console.log('CSRF failed for:', request.url);
      console.log('Headers:', request.headers);
      return new Response('Invalid token', { status: 403 });
    }
  }
}</code></pre>
			
			<h3>Common Error Messages:</h3>
			<div class="error-list">
				<div class="error-item">
					<strong>403 Forbidden</strong>
					<p>→ Missing or invalid CSRF token</p>
				</div>
				<div class="error-item">
					<strong>Cookie not set</strong>
					<p>→ Not in SSR mode, or cookies blocked</p>
				</div>
				<div class="error-item">
					<strong>Token mismatch</strong>
					<p>→ Session expired, or token modified</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>Quick Reference: When to Exclude</h2>
			<table class="decision-table">
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>Scenario</th>
						<th>Exclude?</th>
						<th>Reason</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>User login form</td>
						<td class="no">❌ No</td>
						<td>Uses cookies</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Stripe webhook</td>
						<td class="yes">✅ Yes</td>
						<td>Uses signature</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Public API (API keys)</td>
						<td class="yes">✅ Yes</td>
						<td>No cookies</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Admin panel</td>
						<td class="no">❌ No</td>
						<td>Uses cookies</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Password reset form</td>
						<td class="no">❌ No</td>
						<td>User-facing</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>OAuth callback</td>
						<td class="maybe">⚠️ Maybe</td>
						<td>Depends on flow</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		max-width: 1000px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 2rem;
	}
	
	.back-link {
		display: inline-block;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		color: #0066cc;
		text-decoration: none;
	}
	
	section {
		margin: 3rem 0;
		padding: 2rem;
		background: #f9f9f9;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
	}
	
	h1 {
		font-size: 2.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}
	
	h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		color: #555;
	}
	
	h3 {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem;
	}
	
	.flow-diagram {
		background: white;
		padding: 2rem;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
		margin: 1.5rem 0;
	}
	
	.flow-step {
		background: #f0f0f0;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
		margin: 0.5rem 0;
	}
	
	.flow-step.highlight {
		background: #ffe7e7;
		border: 2px solid #dc3545;
	}
	
	.flow-step strong {
		display: block;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		color: #333;
	}
	
	.flow-step .note {
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		color: #dc3545;
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-top: 0.5rem;
	}
	
	.arrow {
		text-align: center;
		font-size: 2rem;
		color: #666;
		margin: 0.5rem 0;
	}
	
	.warning-box, .tip-box {
		padding: 1.5rem;
		margin: 1.5rem 0;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
	}
	
	.warning-box {
		background: #fff3cd;
		border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
	}
	
	.warning-box h3 {
		margin-top: 0;
		color: #856404;
	}
	
	.tip-box {
		background: #d1ecf1;
		border-left: 4px solid #0c5460;
	}
	
	.tip-box h3 {
		margin-top: 0;
		color: #0c5460;
	}
	
	.comparison-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		margin: 1.5rem 0;
	}
	
	.exclude-yes, .exclude-no {
		background: white;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
	}
	
	.exclude-yes {
		border: 2px solid #28a745;
	}
	
	.exclude-no {
		border: 2px solid #dc3545;
	}
	
	table {
		width: 100%;
		border-collapse: collapse;
		margin: 1.5rem 0;
		background: white;
	}
	
	th, td {
		padding: 1rem;
		text-align: left;
		border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
	}
	
	th {
		background: #f0f0f0;
		font-weight: 600;
	}
	
	.decision-table .yes {
		color: #28a745;
		font-weight: 600;
	}
	
	.decision-table .no {
		color: #dc3545;
		font-weight: 600;
	}
	
	.decision-table .maybe {
		color: #ffc107;
		font-weight: 600;
	}
	
	.error-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin: 1.5rem 0;
	}
	
	.error-item {
		background: white;
		padding: 1rem;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
		border-left: 4px solid #dc3545;
	}
	
	.error-item strong {
		color: #dc3545;
	}
	
	code {
		background: #ffe7e7;
		padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
		border-radius: 0.25rem;
		font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
		font-size: 0.9em;
	}
	
	pre {
		background: #2d2d2d;
		color: #f8f8f2;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
		overflow-x: auto;
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		line-height: 1.5;
		margin: 1rem 0;
	}
	
	pre code {
		background: none;
		padding: 0;
		color: inherit;
	}
	
	ul, ol {
		line-height: 1.8;
	}
	
	li {
		margin: 0.5rem 0;
	}
	
	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.comparison-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
